<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-08T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-08T06:00:00-05:00" n="92" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">255.11 Diamond, Legs/14:Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bremen</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Leonard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bremen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-08T12:00:00+01:00">September 8,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 8—9:35
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Supplementing telegram from Consul at Cologne,<note n="58" xml:id="d92fn58">Not printed.</note> local police authorities inform
                            me John Diamond expelled from Bremen, having sailed from Hamburg
                            Saturday afternoon 6th on freight steamer <hi rend="italic">Hanover</hi>, scheduled to sail directly to Philadelphia arriving there
                            about 20th. He was held in police custody before sailing.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Leonard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>